                    <history>
                        <origin>
                            <origDate notBefore="1700" notAfter="1799">18th century</origDate>
                            According to the colophon on <locus target="#141va"/>, the original owner was
                            <persName ref="PRS14568WaldaKiros" role="patron"/> and 
                            the scribe was <persName ref="PRS14569GadlaGiyorgis" role="scribe"/>.
                            The following family members of <persName ref="PRS14568WaldaKiros" role="patron"/> are mentioned:
                            his father <persName ref="PRS14570Hezqeyas"/>, 
                            his mother <persName ref="PRS14571Ebrawit"/>, and
                            his brother <persName ref="PRS14572Awkatewos"/>. The name of one further brother or sister has been erased.
                        </origin>
                        <provenance>
                            At an unknown point in time, <persName ref="PRS9043Svensson" role="owner">Axel B. Svensson</persName> 
                            aquired
                            the manuscript. He subsequently donated the manuscript to <persName ref="PRS14565ErlingEidem" role="owner">
                                <title>Archbishop</title>
                                Erling Eidem</persName> on <date when="1948-09-15">15 September 1948</date>, according to
                            a type-written note that—at least when the manuscript was catalogued by <persName ref="PRS6337Lofgren"/>—was
                            kept together with the manuscript.
                        </provenance>
                        
                        <acquisition>In <date when="1964">1964</date>, 
